Package: effectcheck
Type: Package
Title: Effect Size Checker for APA-Style Results
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(person(given = "Your", family = "Name", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "you@example.com"))
Description: A conservative, assumption-aware statistical consistency checker for 
    APA-style research results. Parses test statistics, effect sizes, and confidence 
    intervals from text, PDF, HTML, and Word documents. Recomputes effect sizes using 
    all plausible variants when design is ambiguous, and validates internal consistency. 
    Supports t-tests, F-tests/ANOVA, correlations, chi-square, z-tests, regression, 
    and nonparametric tests. Provides statcheck-compatible API functions for batch 
    processing of files and directories. Explicitly tracks all assumptions and 
    uncertainty in output. Detects decision errors (significance reversals) similar 
    to statcheck.
